com.vector.cfg.gen.core.bswmdmodel

Interface GIConfigVariantInfo


  • @NotThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface GIConfigVariantInfo
    BswmdModel ConfigurationVariant information retrieved by the GIModuleConfiguration. Abstraction interface for ConfigurationVariants.
    The class GIConfigVariantInfo provides the information, if a GIModuleConfiguration is post-build selectable. ( isPostBuildSelectable()). 
     

 GIModuleConfiguration moduleBswmdModel=...;

 GIConfigVariantInfo variantInfo = moduleBswmdModel.getConfigVariantInfo();

 if(variantInfo.isPostBuildSelectable()){
     // Do post-build selectable specific code
     //....
 }

    All method parameters must be non-null unless documented otherwise.

      • isLinkTime

        @PublishedMethod
boolean isLinkTime()
        Return true, if the PB-L ConfigurationVariant is LINK-TIME. Otherwise, false.

        Remark:

        The semantic actually is IEcucModuleConfiguration#getConfigurationVariant() == EEcucConfigurationVariant#VARIANT_LINK_TIME. For details read the JavaDoc there.

        Returns:

      • isPostBuildLoadable

        Returns:

      • isPostBuildSelectable

        @PublishedMethod

        Return true, if the module implements post-build selectable. This is equal to calling IEcucModuleConfiguration#supportsPostBuildVariance().
        Returns:

      • isPreCompile
